---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout title="Four Waterfalls Walk - Welsh Hikes">

  <header class="hero">
    <div class="hero-overlay">
      <h1>Four Waterfalls Walk</h1>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="post-wrapper">
    <div class="post-container">

      <div class="meta">
        <span>📍 Brecon Beacons</span>
        <span>📏 9km</span>
        <span>⏱ Approx. 3 hours</span>
        <span>🥾 Moderate</span>
      </div>
      <p class="meta-note">Moderate due to uneven terrain, steps and some steep sections.</p>

      <img class="hero-photo" src="/images/four_waterfalls_large_waterfall.jpeg" alt="The largest waterfall on the Four Waterfalls Walk" />

      <div class="post-body">

        <div class="text-block">
          <p>
            On a sunny but wet weekend in early summer we made the drive out to the Brecon Beacons 
            to take on one of the classic waterfall routes Wales has to offer. After getting 
            lost and taking directions from a farmer on a small tractor, we eventually 
            found the starting point. A quiet car park tucked at the end of a narrow country lane.
          </p>
          <p>
            For the first thirty minutes you are completely surrounded by trees, the constant 
            sound of running water filling the air. There is a moment where you start to wonder 
            whether you have somehow missed the path to the waterfalls entirely. You have not. 
            The route is well marked throughout with wooden signposts and there is no real chance 
            of going wrong.
          </p>
          <p>
            Each waterfall feels bigger than the last, building anticipation as you work your way 
            through the walk. The final one is something else entirely, a gigantic curtain of 
            water pouring over a hanging cliff. What makes it so extraordinary is the underhang. You 
            can actually walk beneath it. It is treacherously loud, the humidity hits you 
            immediately and you will feel the splash of large water droplets, but the experience is
            worth every second of it. The amount of space under there is genuinely surprising.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="side-photo">
          <img src="/images/four_waterfalls_small_waterfall.jpeg" alt="One of the waterfalls along the route" />
        </div>

      </div>

      <p>
        At the base of the final waterfall the water collects into a beautiful pool. 
        There were people swimming when we visited but we were too underprepared to 
        consider joining them at the time, but the option is absolutely there 
        for those who come ready for it.
      </p>

      <a class="route-link" href="https://www.outdooractive.com/en/route/hiking-trail/mid-wales/waterfalls-brecon-beacons/107374043/" target="_blank">
        View Full Route on Outdooractive
      </a>

    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    height: 30vh;
    min-height: 400px;
    background-image: url("/images/four_waterfalls_medium_waterfall.jpeg");
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center 50%;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    border-bottom-left-radius: 50% 8%;
    border-bottom-right-radius: 50% 8%;
    overflow: hidden;
    position: relative;
  }

  .hero::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .hero-overlay {
    padding: 40px 60px;
    text-align: center;
    z-index: 2;
    position: relative;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    color: white;
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .post-wrapper {
    background-color: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 60px 20px;
    min-height: 100vh;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  .post-container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    color: #333;
  }

  .meta {
    display: flex;
    gap: 24px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #555;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  .meta-note {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #888;
    margin: 0 0 28px 0;
  }

  .hero-photo {
    width: 100%;
    max-height: 500px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    object-position: center 60%;
  }

  .post-body {
    display: flex;
    gap: 40px;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }

  .text-block {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .text-block p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .side-photo {
    flex: 0 0 280px;
  }

  .side-photo img {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .post-container > p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }

  .route-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 10px;
    padding: 12px 24px;
    background-color: #003366;
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 1rem;
    transition: background-color 0.3s;
  }

  .route-link:hover {
    background-color: #00509e;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .post-body {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .side-photo {
      flex: 0 0 auto;
      width: 100%;
      order: 1;
    }

    .text-block {
      order: 0;
    }

    .meta {
      gap: 12px;
    }

    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .hero-overlay {
      padding: 20px;
    }
  }
</style>